rite No Matter What draws on popular and scholarly insights into the writing process and stems from Jensen’s experience designing and directing a faculty writing program. With more than three decades as an academic writer, Jensen knows what really helps and hinders the scholarly writing process for scholars in the humanities, social sciences,and sciences. Cut down the academic sword of Damocles, Jensen advises. Learn how to write often and effectively, without pressure or shame. With her encouragement, writers of all levels will find ways to create the writing support they need and deserve.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aAcademic writing. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / General.2bisacsh  aacademic writing advice.  afaculty writing groups.  apublic scholar.  ascholarly writing.  ataming techniques.  awriters block.  awriting issues.  awriting myths.  awriting productivity.  awriting support.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311071193640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226461847423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226461847/original  a978-3-11-071193-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles